    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-08T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-08T18:00:00-05:00" n="742"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.<gloss target="#t_CC1">CC</gloss>(<gloss
                        target="#t_PC1">PC</gloss>)/8–845: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 742<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Alternate Delegate to the Preparatory Commission of the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_GOB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerig</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">restricted</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">u. s. urgent</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-08T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 8, 1945—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6684. <gloss target="#t_Preco1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Preco</hi>
                    </gloss> 23. For <persName corresp="#p_GOB1">Gerig</persName>.</p>
                <p>Our Delegation at the Potsdam Conference is not informed of any discussions
                    relating to Preparatory Commission. British Embassy here seems to be equally
                    uninformed of any discussions of this kind. Have you had any confirmation of the
                    statement made in the first sentence of your 7519, July 26, 11:00 a.m.<note
                        n="1" xml:id="d742fn1">
                        <ref target="#d739">Document No. 739</ref>.</note> and your <gloss
                        target="#t_Copre1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Copre</hi>
                    </gloss> 4 of July 31?<note n="2" xml:id="d742fn2">
                        <ref target="#d741">Document No. 741</ref>.</note> We are naturally
                    interested in any developments relating to the subject of officers of <gloss
                        target="#t_ExeCom1">ExeCom</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_PreCo1"
                        >PreCo</gloss> and would appreciate your communicating any such information
                    urgently.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_BJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                        <lb/>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HA2">A[lger] H[iss]</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
